properties.value:
A creepy hyottoko mask. A rare find!
Anyone else feels like doing a jigsaw puzzle right now?

properties.name: message
properties.value:
A duck, the symbol of all that is. A feathered deity.
This one is just rubber though.

properties.name: message
properties.value:
It's a japanese mayonnaise bottle. The one with the baby doll as a logo.
Luckily, this one is not covered in poop.

properties.name: message
properties.value:
It's a frog... or a girl wearing a frog suit.
Who am I to judge?

properties.name: message
properties.value:
If there's something you can always countn on, it's black hats.
I'll stick with masks though.

properties.name: message
properties.value:
A dancing Kumamon, frozen in time and space.
Pretty underrated.

properties.name: message
properties.value: Just a regular old easter egg. Hidden in plain sight!

properties.name: message
properties.value:
A naked sentient fire showing us it's glorious cheeks.
What has science done...

properties.name: message
properties.value:
A sleeping fox drenched in blue moonlight.
Osaka Castle can't be far off.

properties.name: message
properties.value:
A crystal, humming with a long forgotten tune.
It also tastes of passion.
Fruit.

properties.name: message
properties.value:
The flag of Brazil engraved into a heart shape.
As it should be.

properties.name: message
properties.value:
A weird blueish slipper. Legend has it, that you will encounter bad puns for the rest of eternity.
I'd rather not...

properties.name: message
properties.value: A panda. Classic! That should cover all panda enthusiasts among you.

properties.name: message
properties.value:
And here I thought we wouldn't see this here.
There's no running away.

properties.name: message
properties.value: A stranded land octopus. Patiently waiting to play Elden Ring once again.

properties.name: message
properties.value: A pickaxe used by a joyful dwarf. He mostly plays videogames now, no need for actual mining.

properties.name: message
properties.value:
A roll of black tape.
Perfect for fixing any kind of camera mounts.
